<p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Hi {{lead.First Name:default=there}},</span><br> <br><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Please join us for the webinar, <em><a href="https://content.pivotal.io/webinars/how-to-apply-design-patterns-practices-to-cloud-native-application-development?utm_source=digest&amp;utm_medium=email-link&amp;utm_campaign=design-patterns-q317" target="_blank" style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;">How to Apply Design Patterns &amp; Practices to Cloud-Native Application Development</a>,</em>&nbsp;on September 7, 2017. </span></p> 
<p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: helvetica;">Cloud-native applications are characterized by highly distributed topologies consisting of many relatively small components (yup, usually called microservices). But the thing that sets them apart even more from the previous generation of apps is that they are expected to function flawlessly even while the environment they are running in is constantly changing, or even failing. <br><br> Cornelia Davis, Senior Director of Technology at Pivotal, will share best practices for cloud-native applications and clear some of the mystery that shrouds 12-factor today. At the conclusion, attendees will understand what is needed for cloud-native applications, as well as why and how to deliver on those requirements.<br><br> <strong>Presenter</strong>: Cornelia Davis, Senior Director of Technology at Pivotal</span></p> 
<p><span style="font-family: helvetica; font-size: 14px;"><strong>Date</strong>: Thursday, September 7, 2017<br><strong>Time</strong>: 11:00am PDT / 2:00pm EDT</span></p> 
